        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {marginHistory.map(m => (
          <tr>
            <td>{m.year}</td>
            <td>{m.operating !== 'N/A' ? m.operating + '%' : 'N/A'}</td>
            <td>{m.profit !== 'N/A' ? m.profit + '%' : 'N/A'}</td>
            <td>{m.fcfMargin !== 'N/A' ? m.fcfMargin + '%' : 'N/A'}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS ═══ -->
  <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table class="sensitivity-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
          {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
            <th class={g === roundedGrowth ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(1)}%</th>
          ))}
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
          <tr>
            <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(1)}%</td>
            {row.values.map((v, i) => (
              <td class={row.dr === discountRate && sensitivityGrowth[i] === roundedGrowth ? 'current' : ''}>
                ${v}
              </td>
            ))}
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
  <h2>Risks & What the Model Misses</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Acquisition Spree:</strong> Synopsys heavily utilizes M&A (e.g., Ansys acquisition). Large debt financing from acquisitions can alter the WACC significantly and dilute current cash flow bases.</li>
    <li><strong>Cyclical Semiconductor Downswings:</strong> While EDA tools are sticky, massive industry pullbacks in semiconductor R&D budgets could stall growth.</li>
    <li><strong>China Export Restrictions:</strong> Geopolitical tensions and export controls can restrict Synopsys from selling its most advanced EDA software to a significant market segment.</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Why use a mathematically derived Discount Rate instead of a flat 10%?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Synopsys's risk profile dynamically interacts with interest rates. Using CAPM (Risk-Free Rate + Beta * ERP) roots the required return in empirical data rather than arbitrary benchmarks.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How do you handle recent large debt issuance?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">The model deducts Total Debt dynamically from the enterprise value. If recent debt (e.g., for an acquisition) has spiked, it instantly reduces the Equity Value per share calculation, capturing the risk natively.</div>
    </details>
  </div>

